# .clinerules — ~/.zsh dotfiles

## What This Repo Is
Personal zsh-focused dotfiles used across macOS and Ubuntu environments.
It contains shell startup files, aliases/functions, helper scripts, tmux/terminal config,
and direnv setup for personal project trees.

## Canonical Layout
```
~/.zsh/
  zshrc, zprofile, zshenv      # core shell startup files
  aliases                      # common aliases
  functions/                   # reusable zsh helper functions (*.sh in this repo)
  scripts/                     # user-invoked helper scripts
  envrc/                       # shared direnv files, symlinked into project repos
  memory-bank/                 # cross-session AI state/context
  fzf-shell/                   # fzf completion + keybindings
```

## Repo Conventions
- Prefer `~/.local/bin/` for user binaries/symlinks; treat `~/bin/` references as legacy.
- Keep automation logic in `scripts/`; keep shell sourcing/config in root files.
- Do not add project-specific logic to `direnvrc`; keep it in `envrc/*.envrc`.
- `envrc/` files are the source of truth; project-local `.envrc` files should be symlinks.

## Current envrc Pattern
- `envrc/personal.envrc` is shared baseline for personal repos.
  - macOS (`uname -s == Darwin`): run both `sync-claude` and `sync-gemini`.
  - non-macOS: run `sync-gemini` only.
- `envrc/k3d-manager.envrc` does:
  - `source_up`
  - appends local `bin/` to `PATH`
  - sets `git config core.hooksPath scripts/hooks`
  - exports agent lint mapping vars (`AGENT_LINT_GATE_VAR`, `AGENT_LINT_AI_FUNC`)

## Script/Style Guidelines
- For shell scripts: include strict mode (`set -euo pipefail`) unless intentionally incompatible.
- Prefer short hyphenated script names in `scripts/`.
- Keep line length near <=100 chars and indentation consistent (2 spaces preferred).
- Reuse existing clipboard/tmux patterns (`scripts/yank`, `scripts/put`) instead of creating duplicates.

## Security Rules
- Never commit secrets (tokens, passwords, private keys, machine-specific creds).
- Never commit `.envrc.local` (local secrets belong there, outside git).
- Sanitize shareable output with `scripts/sanitize.sh` (uses `sanitize.sed`).
- Treat `services-output/` as sensitive output area; scrub before sharing.

## Agent Operating Rules
- Claude owns writes to `memory-bank/`; keep entries concise and factual.
- When adding/changing scripts, update memory-bank context with purpose and usage.
- Prefer non-destructive edits and preserve behavior unless task asks for functional change.
- Validate shell edits with:
  - `zsh -n <file>` for zsh files
  - `shellcheck scripts/<file>` for shell scripts when applicable
